# .trunk Template

To set up the `.trunk` repository, follow these steps:

1. Clone the `.trunk-template` repository:
   ```
   git clone https://github.com/trunk-io/.trunk-template.git
   ```

2. Create a new repository for your project on GitHub.

3. Copy the contents of the `.trunk-template` repository to your new repository.

4. Customize the `.trunk` configuration file:
   - Open the `.trunk` file in your new repository.
   - Update the necessary configuration options according to your project's requirements.

5. Commit and push the changes to your new repository.

6. Configure Trunk Check to monitor your repository:
   - Go to the Trunk Check website (https://trunk.io).
   - Sign in with your GitHub account.
   - Add your repository to Trunk Check.

7. Trunk Check will now start monitoring your repository for issues and pull requests.

For more information, refer to the Trunk Check documentation: [https://docs.trunk.io/docs/check-github-integration](https://docs.trunk.io/docs/check-github-integration)
